&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director of Merchandising, EU is responsible for leading and scaling the product assortment strategy for the European region. This senior leadership role drives the identification of high-potential brands, develops strategic vendor partnerships, secures best-in-class commercial terms, and leverages data-driven insights to accelerate category growth and regional revenue performance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-impact, builder role. The Director leads and grows the EU Merchandising team, drives cross-functional collaboration with Supply Chain, Commercial, Compliance, and Finance, and ensures the European business is set up to win commercially, operationally, and strategically.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Expectations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the EU Merchandising strategy — assortment, category priorities, vendor portfolio, and commercial performance across the European market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, lead, and develop the EU Merchandising team, creating a data-driven, results-oriented culture aligned with iHerb’s growth ambitions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report to the EU General Manager and contribute actively to the EU Leadership Team, driving cross-functional alignment on business priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with the VP of Merchandising (dotted line) and Directors to ensure EU strategy operates within the global framework and leverages global capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive category growth through assortment optimization, competitive pricing, promotions, and vendor negotiations that deliver strong margin outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead regional vendor partnerships — identifying high-potential brands, securing best-in-class commercial terms, and building long-term supplier relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Supply Chain and Inventory Management on forecasting, vendor performance, order cycles, and in-stock execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Commercial and Finance teams to ensure EU merchandising decisions are commercially sound and support revenue and profitability targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Compliance and Regulatory teams to manage catalog additions, documentation, and approvals in line with EU requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adapt global merchandising strategies to EU customer needs, market trends, and regulatory standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use analytics and category insights to identify growth opportunities, guide decisions, and drive continuous improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The duties and responsibilities described above may provide only a partial description of this position. This is not an exhaustive list of all aspects of the job.&amp;nbsp; Other duties and responsibilities not outlined in this document may be added as necessary or desirable, with or without notice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Knowledge, Skills and abilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven leadership and team-building capability, with experience managing and developing merchandising or buying teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial acumen with a track record of delivering category growth and margin performance in an eCommerce environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled negotiator with the ability to secure strong vendor terms and build lasting supplier partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive presence and the ability to influence at all levels — from vendors to senior leadership and cross-functional peers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of EU market dynamics, regulatory requirements, and consumer needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced analytical skills and data-driven mindset to guide decisions and spot opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong cross-functional collaborator, especially with Supply Chain, Finance, Commercial, and Compliance&lt;/li&gt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director, Product Management - Global Customer Experience will lead the global digital customer experience across desktop web, mobile web, and native apps. This role will oversee product strategy, roadmap execution, experimentation, and cross-functional delivery for key commerce experiences including Product Detail Pages (PDPs) for new and returning users, User Generated Content (UGC), SEO / GEO / SEM product experiences, Product cards and merchandising surfaces, Product comparison capabilities, Cross-sell and upsell experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Expectations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Strategy &amp;amp; Vision&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive the global product vision, strategy, and roadmap for customer experience initiatives across desktop, mobile web, and native apps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build differentiated shopping experiences that improve product discovery, trust, engagement, conversion, and customer retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop customer-centric strategies tailored for both new and returning users throughout the shopping journey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify emerging industry trends, AI-driven commerce opportunities, personalization capabilities, and competitive differentiators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Ownership Areas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Detail Pages (PDPs)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end PDP experiences for:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New customer acquisition journeys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Returning customer engagement and conversion optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize content hierarchy, merchandising, trust signals, personalization, and conversion levers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive experimentation around pricing visibility, recommendations, bundling, subscriptions, and purchase confidence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;User Generated Content (UGC)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead strategy for ratings, reviews, Q&amp;amp;A, customer photos/videos, and community engagement experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve trust, content quality, moderation frameworks, and conversion impact of UGC.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with AI/ML teams to enhance content summarization, sentiment extraction, and relevance ranking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SEO / GEO / SEM Experiences&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Growth, Marketing, and Engineering teams to optimize organic and paid acquisition landing experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive technical SEO product enhancements including indexing, structured data, internal linking, page performance, and discoverability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support global localization and geo-targeted experiences to improve search visibility and customer acquisition efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate on SEM landing page optimization and conversion funnel improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Cards &amp;amp; Merchandising Components&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the strategy and performance of product cards across search, category, recommendation, and merchandising surfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve information density, personalization, visual hierarchy, promotional messaging, and engagement metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize mobile-first browsing experiences and scalable merchandising systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Comparison Features&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and launch product comparison experiences that simplify decision-making and increase customer confidence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable frameworks for feature comparisons, attribute matching, alternative recommendations, and buying guidance.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director, Product Management – Global Store Discovery will lead the global digital shopping discovery experience across desktop web, mobile web, and native apps. This role will own the strategy, roadmap execution, experimentation, and cross-functional delivery for the core discovery surfaces that connect customers with products across iHerb’s global platform. Key areas of ownership include the Homepage, Search (including AI-powered search), Product Listing Pages (PLPs), Navigation, Promotional and Campaign landing experiences, Personalized discovery feeds, and other browse and discovery surfaces across the site and app.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Expectations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Strategy &amp;amp; Vision&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Define and drive the global product vision, strategy, and roadmap for store discovery experiences across desktop, mobile web, and native apps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build differentiated discovery experiences that improve product findability, browsing engagement, conversion, and customer retention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop customer-centric strategies tailored for both new and returning users across the full discovery journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identify emerging trends in AI-powered search, personalization, recommendation engines, and competitive discovery experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Ownership Areas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Homepage&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own the global homepage experience as the primary brand and discovery entry point.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Drive strategy for content layout, personalization, promotional placement, featured categories, localization and curated product surfaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Optimize for engagement, new user acquisition, and returning customer activation across all devices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Partner with Merchandising and Marketing to enable scalable content operations and campaign execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Search&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own the end-to-end search frontend product experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Drive AI/ML-powered search improvements including semantic search, vector-based retrieval and AI driven shopping experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Partner with Data Science and Engineering to continuously improve search quality metrics and conversion rates from search.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support multilingual and global search experiences across all iHerb markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Listing Pages (PLPs)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own PLP experiences across category pages, brand pages, promotion pages, and search results pages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Optimize product card layouts, sorting and filtering options, pagination, and information hierarchy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Drive personalization of PLP ranking and product sequencing based on behavioral and contextual signals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Improve mobile-first browsing and grid/list display experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Partner with Merchandising on promotional badging, deals visibility, and category curation strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Navigation &amp;amp; Site S

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift: 2C&lt;br data-start=&quot;9&quot; data-end=&quot;12&quot;&gt;Schedule: Monday, Tuesday, Thursday &amp;amp; Friday | 6:00 PM – 4:00 AM&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Job Summary:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Under general supervision, the Maintenance Technician is responsible for performing highly diversified duties to install, troubleshoot, repair and maintain production and facility equipment according to safety, predictive and productive maintenance systems and processes to support the achievement of the site’s business goals and objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Expectations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perform highly diversified duties to install and maintain production machines and the plant facility’s equipment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide emergency/unscheduled repairs of production equipment during production and performs scheduled maintenance repairs of production equipment during machine service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perform simple machinist duties and responsibilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perform mechanic skills including, but not limited to, mechanical, electrical, pneumatic, hydraulic, troubleshooting and repair of production machines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Read and interpret equipment manuals and work orders to perform required maintenance and service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diagnose problems, replace or repair parts, test and make adjustments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perform regular preventive maintenance on machines, equipment and plant facilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perform a variety of plumbing maintenance and carpentry functions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use a variety of hand and power tools, electric meters and material handling equipment in performing duties&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Detect faulty operations, defective material and report those and any unusual situations to proper supervision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comply with safety regulations and maintain clean and orderly work areas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
