&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Expectations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute integrated marketing initiatives for the Korea market in alignment with regional and global business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage external agencies across &lt;strong&gt;social media, influencer marketing, and promotional asset development&lt;/strong&gt; to ensure high-quality and timely execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee iHerb&#39;s local social media presence, including KakaoTalk, Instagram, and YouTube, while driving audience engagement and brand growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate influencer marketing campaigns from planning through execution and performance review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with Global Marketing, Paid Media, Creative, and other internal stakeholders to deliver localized marketing campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multiple marketing projects simultaneously, ensuring priorities, timelines, and deliverables are executed efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor campaign performance and provide actionable recommendations to improve marketing effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date with Korean market trends and identify opportunities to strengthen iHerb&#39;s local marketing presence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge, Skills and Abilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
